  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Digital Marketing Applications,\" published by Peter Lang Verlag in 2019, stands as a noteworthy contribution to the field despite limited academic citations and public engagement. Its potential as a pedagogical anchor is enhanced by its commercial presence on platforms like Amazon and Goodreads, though it lacks significant visibility in social discourse and traditional scholarly uptake metrics.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Digital Marketing Applications\" has entered the academic landscape with a modest citation footprint, registering three citations since its publication in 2019. While citations often reflect scholarly engagement, the book's current impact metrics suggest a limited reach within academic circles. This is indeed a challenge in understanding its influence on the body of knowledge in digital marketing.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book appears to have been positioned predominantly within commercial channels, as evidenced by strong presence indicators on platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads. This commercial linkage indicates its utility in educational contexts, catering to audiences interested in digital marketing applications, albeit lacking comprehensive data regarding community discourse or public engagement on social platforms.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">Furthermore, \"Digital Marketing Applications\" is characterized by a noteworthy inferred role as a pedagogical anchor, with evidence supporting its use in libraries and potentially in educational offerings, particularly online. Despite the absence of open educational resources (OER) listings, the presence in library holdings suggests an intentionality behind its utility in curricular settings, thus reinforcing its pedagogical value.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">In summary, while \"Digital Marketing Applications\" has made strides in commercial visibility and pedagogical applications, it faces challenges in academic uptake and online community discussions. The work\u2019s engagement within library systems may offer a pathway for future influence as educators and learners continue to seek relevant resources in the evolving digital marketing domain.</p>",
